3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a mixture of experts formulation to predict saliency.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses convolutional neural networks to gather local information.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with visual saliency prediction, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
